# Backstage Pro — Supabase Rules

## Schema das tabelas principais
```
profiles:    id(uuid PK), name, phone, city, state, category, category_label,
             specialties(text[]), years_experience, daily_rate,
             monthly_goal_events, monthly_goal_revenue, onboarding_complete

clients:     id, user_id(FK), name, email, phone, contact_person,
             logo_url, company, city, state, notes, is_favorite,
             default_daily_cache, policy_default_payment_model

events:      id, user_id(FK), client_id(FK), title, start_date, end_date,
             daily_cache_value, cache_valor_base, payment_model,
             status, payment_status, paid_amount, paid_date,
             auto_hours_applied, description, location

expenses:    id, user_id(FK), event_id(FK), title, category, amount,
             expense_date, payment_method, notes, receipt_url

daily_work:  id, user_id(FK), event_id(FK), work_date, entry_time, exit_time,
             hours_worked, overtime_hours, daily_cache, notes, photo_url, status

user_settings: id, user_id(FK UNIQUE), theme, notifications_enabled,
               email_notifications, currency, language, timezone
```

## Mapeamentos legados (useDailyWork)
- DB usa `work_date` e `hours_worked` — hook expõe como `date` e `total_hours`
- DB usa `description` — hook expõe como `notes`
- Sempre usar os campos do hook, nunca acessar DB diretamente

## Criação de hooks — padrão
```js
export function useEntidade() {
  const { user } = useAuth();
  const userId = user?.id;
  const [items, setItems] = useState([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  // refetch, create (injeta user_id, deleta owner_id), update, remove
  return { items, loading, error, refetch, create, update, delete: remove };
}
```

## RLS — regra universal
